DESIGN CATALOG TABLES
 db_types
  => mvcc_hdr, id, name, size(used only for primitve signed/unsigned integral, bit_field and float types)
  * if the id < 10000, then it is permanent and can not be deleted

 db_attributes
  => mvcc_hdr, id, name, type_id, rel_pos_in_type, count (0->variable length, 1->direct-element, N->fixed length array of N elements), is_nullable, default_value, derived_from_expression(for derived columns of table and index expressions)
  * append only table

 db_tables
  => mvcc_hdr, id, version(increments on every alter statements), name, type_id, root_page_id, blobs_root_page_id
  * only add column and drop column supported
  * rel_pos_in_type is only incremented on add column in a new type on copy
  * on drop a clone is done for all attributes and the type_id and a row from this clone is dropped
  * default value and is nullable changes are made in place
  * to create a new partition, insert a new entry here with a new root_page_id and a new cloned type_id and attributes

 db_indices
  => mvcc_hdr, id, name, table_id, key_type_id, root_page_id
  * key_type_id implicitly has tuple_pointer (heap_table_root_page_id, page_id, tuple_index) in it for uniqueness and to find the actual tuples in the heap_table

 db_ref_counters
  * root_page_id, reference_count, tuple_def, key_element_ids, key_element_count, object_type (bplus_tree, hash_table, heap_table, blob_store)
  * delete the underlying data structure only if the reference_counter reaches 0
  * stores root_page_id and reference_count for all non system tables

 db_schema_blobs (blob_store for storing default value or tuple_defs)

 db_name_index
  * name, db_object_type, tuple_pointer

